      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CRUISIN' GRAE (3) showed blistering pace early and gave a sight when in the minors, beaten 1.5 lengths over 390m this track in 22.26. Can go on with it. BIG BOY PANTS (1) has a fair record and proved too classy last time to win by 1.3 lengths at Ballarat in a handy 22.05 beating Reiko Comet. Has performed well from this box with a win and two minor placings to his name from three starts. Has hit winning form and can go on with it. I'M TO BLAME (2) drew an outside box and was game in defeat when only 1.3 lengths from the winner Moraine Koby in second(22.29) at this track. The form from his last run stacks up well. Must be included in calculations. ASTON CURRENCY (4) is going well, finishing in the placings twice in a row. Not beaten far last time when a 1.3 lengths third (22.29) in a Grade 5 at this track.",
